sBTAIdentFirmwareRev.name: sBTAIdentFirmwareRev
sBTAIdentFirmwareRev.description: An 8 byte ID string identifying the DS72 firmware revision. This value is set at the factory.

sBTAIdentSerialNumber.name: sBTAIdentSerialNumber
sBTAIdentSerialNumber.description: A number identifying the serial number of the DS72. This value is set at the factory.

sBTAIdentUnitName.name: sBTAIdentUnitName
sBTAIdentUnitName.description: A 64-character string identifying the name (UnitID) of the DS72. This value is set at the factory to a default of DS72.

sBTANetworkConfigBootpEnable.name: sBTANetworkConfigBootpEnable
sBTANetworkConfigBootpEnable.description: Enables/disables bootp. Bootp will not take effect until the unit is reseted.

sBTANetworkConfigDHCPEnable.name: sBTANetworkConfigDHCPEnable
sBTANetworkConfigDHCPEnable.description: Enables/disables DHCP. DHCP will not take effect until the unit is reseted.

sBTANetworkConfigSSHEnable.name: sBTANetworkConfigSSHEnable
sBTANetworkConfigSSHEnable.description: Enables/disables SSH logins. Disable/enable SSH will take effect after the unit is reseted.

sBTANetworkConfigActivityTimeout.name: sBTANetworkConfigActivityTimeout
sBTANetworkConfigActivityTimeout.description: A value from 0 to 120. 0 disables activity timeouts. Value represents minutes of non-activity before telnet / SSH sessions are automatically logged out. Default is 0.

sBTANetworkConfigDirectConnEnable.name: sBTANetworkConfigDirectConnEnable
sBTANetworkConfigDirectConnEnable.description: Enables/disables direct port connection upon login.

sBTANetworkConfigSNMPReadOnlyCommunity.name: sBTANetworkConfigSNMPReadOnlyCommunity
sBTANetworkConfigSNMPReadOnlyCommunity.description: The community name to use for read only access. Maximum len 16 bytes.

sBTANetworkConfigSNMPReadWriteCommunity.name: sBTANetworkConfigSNMPReadWriteCommunity
sBTANetworkConfigSNMPReadWriteCommunity.description: The community name to use for read-write access. Maximum len 16 bytes.

sBTANetworkConfigSNMPNumTrapReceivers.name: sBTANetworkConfigSNMPNumTrapReceivers
sBTANetworkConfigSNMPNumTrapReceivers.description: The maximum number of managers to send traps to. Currently 4.

sBTANetworkConfigSNMPTrapReceiverTable.name: sBTANetworkConfigSNMPTrapReceiverTable
sBTANetworkConfigSNMPTrapReceiverTable.description: A list of managers to send traps to. The number of entries is given by the value of sBTANetworkConfigSNMPNumTrapReceivers. Maximum number of Trap Receivers is four.

sBTANetworkConfigSNMPTrapReceiverEntry.name: sBTANetworkConfigSNMPTrapReceiverEntry
sBTANetworkConfigSNMPTrapReceiverEntry.description: Table of managers to send traps to.

trapIndex.name: trapIndex
trapIndex.description: The index to a trap receiver entry.

receiverAddress.name: receiverAddress
receiverAddress.description: The IP address of the manager to send traps to.

sBTANetworkConfigRadiusPrimaryServer.name: sBTANetworkConfigRadiusPrimaryServer
sBTANetworkConfigRadiusPrimaryServer.description: Ip address of the primary RADIUS server.

sBTANetworkConfigRadiusSecondaryServer.name: sBTANetworkConfigRadiusSecondaryServer
sBTANetworkConfigRadiusSecondaryServer.description: Ip address of the back-up RADIUS server.

sBTANetworkConfigRadiusLocalLogin.name: sBTANetworkConfigRadiusLocalLogin
sBTANetworkConfigRadiusLocalLogin.description: Enables / disables the use of local (usernames stored in the DS72) logins in the case that both the primary and secondary RADIUS server are not available.

sBTANetworkConfigWebActivityTimeout.name: sBTANetworkConfigWebActivityTimeout
sBTANetworkConfigWebActivityTimeout.description: A value from 0 to 120. 0 disables WEB activity timeouts. Value represents minutes of non-activity before WEB sessions are automatically logged out. Default is 0.

sBTAModulesNumberOfModules.name: sBTAModulesNumberOfModules
sBTAModulesNumberOfModules.description: Number of modules installed into the DS unit.

sBTAModulesModulesInstalled.name: sBTAModulesModulesInstalled
sBTAModulesModulesInstalled.description: A character string listing the modules installed seperated by commas. Each module is identifed by a two digit number indicating the slot. For example 02,03,04,06 means modules 2,3,4 and 6 are installed.

sBTAModulesResetModulesCmd.name: sBTAModulesResetModulesCmd
sBTAModulesResetModulesCmd.description: This command is no longer supported.

sBTAModulesNumberOfIntelligentModules.name: sBTAModulesNumberOfIntelligentModules
sBTAModulesNumberOfIntelligentModules.description: The number of Intelligent Modules installed in the DS Unit.

sBTAModulesNumberOfRPCModules.name: sBTAModulesNumberOfRPCModules
sBTAModulesNumberOfRPCModules.description: The number of DS30 Modules installed in the DS Unit.

sBTAModulesRPCTable.name: sBTAModulesRPCTable
sBTAModulesRPCTable.description: Allows for control of individual outlets and individual RPC modules.

sBTAModulesRPCEntry.name: sBTAModulesRPCEntry
sBTAModulesRPCEntry.description: The RPCs to control and get status on.

sBTAModulesRPCIndex.name: sBTAModulesRPCIndex
sBTAModulesRPCIndex.description: The index into the RPC table. Indexes for rpcs attached to ds74 modules are calculate with the following formula: ((module - 2) * 4) + port. For example module 3 port 1 = index 5.

sBTAModulesRPCName.name: sBTAModulesRPCName
sBTAModulesRPCName.description: The name (unit id) of the rpc.

sBTAModulesRPCFirmwareVersion.name: sBTAModulesRPCFirmwareVersion
sBTAModulesRPCFirmwareVersion.description: The firware version of the rpc.

sBTAModulesRPCCurrent.name: sBTAModulesRPCCurrent
sBTAModulesRPCCurrent.description: The current reading for the power strip. If current measurement is not installed this value will always read 0.

sBTAModulesRPCMaxCurrent.name: sBTAModulesRPCMaxCurrent
sBTAModulesRPCMaxCurrent.description: The maximum detected current reading for the power strip. If current measurement is not installed this value will always read 0. Setting this value to 0 will clear the maximum current detected.

sBTAModulesRPCVoltage.name: sBTAModulesRPCVoltage
sBTAModulesRPCVoltage.description: The voltage reading for the power strip. If voltage measurement is not installed this value will always read 0.

sBTAModulesRPCPower.name: sBTAModulesRPCPower
sBTAModulesRPCPower.description: The power reading for the power strip. If power measurement is not installed this value will always read 0.

sBTAModulesRPCTemperature.name: sBTAModulesRPCTemperature
sBTAModulesRPCTemperature.description: The temperature reading for the power strip. Readings are in degrees C. If temperature measurement is not installed this value will always read 0.

sBTAModulesRPCRebootTimeout.name: sBTAModulesRPCRebootTimeout
sBTAModulesRPCRebootTimeout.description: The length of off time for automatic reboot sequences. Currently a read-only value set to the fixed reboot timeout.

sBTAModulesRPCAllOutletsCmd.name: sBTAModulesRPCAllOutletsCmd
sBTAModulesRPCAllOutletsCmd.description: Turns all outlets on, off or reboot. 0 = off 1 = on 2 = reboot A get will return unknown (6).

sBTAModulesRPCAllOutletsStatus.name: sBTAModulesRPCAllOutletsStatus
sBTAModulesRPCAllOutletsStatus.description: Reports status of outlets in a comma deliminated string. 0 = off 1 = on 2 = reboot 3 = locked on 4 = locked off

sBTAModulesRPCCurrentAlarmThreshold.name: sBTAModulesRPCCurrentAlarmThreshold
sBTAModulesRPCCurrentAlarmThreshold.description: The current alarm threshold level *10. A value of 105 will set the level to 10.5.

sBTAModulesRPCOverVoltageThreshold.name: sBTAModulesRPCOverVoltageThreshold
sBTAModulesRPCOverVoltageThreshold.description: The over voltage alarm threshold level *10. A value of 105 will set the level to 10.5.

sBTAModulesRPCUnderVoltageThreshold.name: sBTAModulesRPCUnderVoltageThreshold
sBTAModulesRPCUnderVoltageThreshold.description: The under voltage alarm threshold level *10. A value of 105 will set the level to 10.5.

sBTAModulesRPCNumberOfOutlets.name: sBTAModulesRPCNumberOfOutlets
sBTAModulesRPCNumberOfOutlets.description: Number of outlets for this RPC. This will be the size of outlet table for this RPC index.

sBTAModulesRPCCircuitBreaker.name: sBTAModulesRPCCircuitBreaker
sBTAModulesRPCCircuitBreaker.description: Status of circuit breaker in power strip. 0=off 1=on.

sBTAModulesRPCOverTempThreshold.name: sBTAModulesRPCOverTempThreshold
sBTAModulesRPCOverTempThreshold.description: The over temperature alarm threshold level *10. A value of 505 will set the level to 50.5.

sBTAModulesRPCNumberOfBreakers.name: sBTAModulesRPCNumberOfBreakers
sBTAModulesRPCNumberOfBreakers.description: Number of breakers for this RPC.

sBTAModulesRPCLowCurrentThreshold.name: sBTAModulesRPCLowCurrentThreshold
sBTAModulesRPCLowCurrentThreshold.description: Low current threshold for this RPC.

sBTAModulesRPCSourceSwitchCount.name: sBTAModulesRPCSourceSwitchCount
sBTAModulesRPCSourceSwitchCount.description: Count of Voltage Source Switches for this RPC.

sBTAModulesRPCNumberOfSensors.name: sBTAModulesRPCNumberOfSensors
sBTAModulesRPCNumberOfSensors.description: Number of environmental sensors for this RPC.

sBTAModulesRPCType.name: sBTAModulesRPCType
sBTAModulesRPCType.description: The type of RPC installed at the indexed location.

sBTAModulesRPCOutletTable.name: sBTAModulesRPCOutletTable
sBTAModulesRPCOutletTable.description: Allows for control of individual outlets. The number of entries is contained in the sBTAModulesRPCOutletTableSize OID.

sBTAModulesRPCOutletEntry.name: sBTAModulesRPCOutletEntry
sBTAModulesRPCOutletEntry.description: The outlets to control and get status on.

sBTAModulesRPCOutletModuleIndex.name: sBTAModulesRPCOutletModuleIndex
sBTAModulesRPCOutletModuleIndex.description: The index to the outlet entry.

sBTAModulesRPCOutletIndex.name: sBTAModulesRPCOutletIndex
sBTAModulesRPCOutletIndex.description: The index to the outlet entry.

sBTAModulesRPCOutletState.name: sBTAModulesRPCOutletState
sBTAModulesRPCOutletState.description: Getting this variable will return the state of the outlet. Valid return states are unknown, on, off, lockon, lockoff. 0 = off 1 = on 2 = reboot 3 = lockon (outlet is on and no changes are allowed) 4 = lockoff (outlet is off and no changes are allowed) 5 = unlock.

sBTAModulesRPCOutletName.name: sBTAModulesRPCOutletName
sBTAModulesRPCOutletName.description: The name of the outlet. Maximum size is 16 characters.

sBTAModulesRPCGroupCmd.name: sBTAModulesRPCGroupCmd
sBTAModulesRPCGroupCmd.description: A character string listing the outlets that need to be controlled, turned off, or turn on as a group. Command is the first character followed by a space. Valid commads are 0=off,1=on, or 2=reboot. A list follows the command in the format module.outlet. For example 2 2.1,2.12,3.1 will reboot module 2 outlet 2&12 module 3 outlet 1.

sBTAModulesRPCCurrentGroupsCurrentTable.name: sBTAModulesRPCCurrentGroupsCurrentTable
sBTAModulesRPCCurrentGroupsCurrentTable.description: A list of total current for RPCs in each current group

sBTAModulesRPCCurrentGroupsCurrentEntry.name: sBTAModulesRPCCurrentGroupsCurrentEntry
sBTAModulesRPCCurrentGroupsCurrentEntry.description: Table of total current measurement by group

groupCurrentIndex.name: groupCurrentIndex
groupCurrentIndex.description: The index to a group total current.

groupCurrent.name: groupCurrent
groupCurrent.description: Current total for all RPCs in group.

rpcGroup.name: rpcGroup
rpcGroup.description: A character string listing the RPCs, by port index, that will be included in a measurement of total current. For each group, a sum will be periodically computed of currents of all listed RPCs, which will be compared to warning and emergency thresholds, generating appropriate traps as required by transit of a threshold. A maximum of 8 RPCs may be monitored within a group. The RPC must be connected and operating and the corresponding DS74 serial port must be configured for an RPC-SNMP device type to be allowed group membership.

warningThreshold.name: warningThreshold
warningThreshold.description: The current level, in tenths of an amp, that will cause a Current Level Warning trap to be sent if the total current for the associated group if exceeded. Conversely, a Current Level Warning Clear trap will be sent whent the total group current falls below the threshold.

emergencyThreshold.name: emergencyThreshold
emergencyThreshold.description: The current level, in tenths of an amp, that will cause a Current Level Emergency trap to be sent if the total current for the associated group if exceeded. Conversely, a Current Level Emergeny Clear trap will be sent whent the total group current falls below the threshold.

sBTAModulesRPCBreakersTable.name: sBTAModulesRPCBreakersTable
sBTAModulesRPCBreakersTable.description: Allows monitoring of individual outlet strips on RPCs.

sBTAModulesRPCBreakersModulesIndex.name: sBTAModulesRPCBreakersModulesIndex
sBTAModulesRPCBreakersModulesIndex.description: The index into the RPC table.

sBTAModulesRPCBreakersBreakersIndex.name: sBTAModulesRPCBreakersBreakersIndex
sBTAModulesRPCBreakersBreakersIndex.description: The index into the RPC breaker table.

sBTAModulesRPCBreakersCircuitBreaker.name: sBTAModulesRPCBreakersCircuitBreaker
sBTAModulesRPCBreakersCircuitBreaker.description: Status of circuit breaker in power strip. 0=off 1=on.

sBTAModulesRPCBreakersCurrent.name: sBTAModulesRPCBreakersCurrent
sBTAModulesRPCBreakersCurrent.description: The detected current reading for the power strip. If current measurement is not installed this value will always read 0.

sBTAModulesRPCBreakersMaxCurrent.name: sBTAModulesRPCBreakersMaxCurrent
sBTAModulesRPCBreakersMaxCurrent.description: The maximum detected current reading for the power strip. If current measurement is not installed this value will always read 0.

sBTAModulesRPCBreakersVoltage.name: sBTAModulesRPCBreakersVoltage
sBTAModulesRPCBreakersVoltage.description: The voltage reading for the power strip. If voltage measurement is not installed this value will always read 0.

sBTAModulesRPCBreakersPower.name: sBTAModulesRPCBreakersPower
sBTAModulesRPCBreakersPower.description: The power reading for the power strip. If voltage measurement is not installed this value will always read 0.

sBTAModulesRPCBreakersVA.name: sBTAModulesRPCBreakersVA
sBTAModulesRPCBreakersVA.description: The volt-amps reading for the power strip. If voltage measurement is not installed this value will always read 0.

sBTAModulesRPCBreakersCurrentAlarmThresh.name: sBTAModulesRPCBreakersCurrentAlarmThreshold
sBTAModulesRPCBreakersCurrentAlarmThresh.description: The current alarm threshold level *10. A value of 105 will set the level to 10.5.

sBTAControlResetUnit.name: sBTAControlResetUnit
sBTAControlResetUnit.description: Setting this value to 1 will cause the unit to reset. A get of this OID will return 0.

sBTAControlResetModules.name: sBTAControlResetModules
sBTAControlResetModules.description: Setting this value to 1 will cause the unit to reset modules simular to the telnet RM command. A get of this OID will return 0.

sBTAControlNumOfLoggedUsers.name: sBTAControlNumOfLoggedUsers
sBTAControlNumOfLoggedUsers.description: Number of users logged in via telnet or SSH.

sBTAControlUserTable.name: sBTAControlUserTable
sBTAControlUserTable.description: A list of users and user information. The number of entries is contained in the sBTAControlNumOfLoggedUsers OID.

sBTAControlUserEntry.name: sBTAControlUserEntry
sBTAControlUserEntry.description: The users to get status on.

sBTAControlUserIndex.name: sBTAControlUserIndex
sBTAControlUserIndex.description: The index to the user entry.

sBTAControlUserAddress.name: sBTAControlUserAddress
sBTAControlUserAddress.description: The IP address of the user.

sBTAControlUserConnection.name: sBTAControlUserConnection
sBTAControlUserConnection.description: Type of connection. If unknown, user is logging out or the connection is invalid.

sBTAControlUserConnModule.name: sBTAControlUserConnModule
sBTAControlUserConnModule.description: If the user is connected to a module, this value will report the module number connected to. If the value is 0 the user is not connected to a module.

sBTAControlUserConnPort.name: sBTAControlUserConnPort
sBTAControlUserConnPort.description: The port number with in a module that the user is connected to. This usually only applies to connections to DS74 serial modules. Intelligent modules connections are always made on port 1. If value is 0 the user is not connected to a module.

sBTAControlUserTerminateUser.name: sBTAControlUserTerminateUser
sBTAControlUserTerminateUser.description: Settings this OID to anything but 0 will terminate (log out) the user. A get of this OID will return 0.

sBTAFileTransferEnableUpgradeFTPFileTran.name: sBTAFileTransferEnableUpgradeFTPFileTransfer
sBTAFileTransferEnableUpgradeFTPFileTran.description: Setting this OID to enableUpgradeFileTransferDownloadViaFTP (1) will start the FTP server and place the DS72 in upgrade mode. An FTP connection may then be established for the purpose of transmitting a firmware upgrade file.

mtrapargsInteger.name: mtrapargsInteger
mtrapargsInteger.description: This OID allows baytech traps to be sent with an integer argument that may not be defined in the baytech MIB. A get of this OID will return 0.

mtrapargsIpAddress.name: mtrapargsIpAddress
mtrapargsIpAddress.description: This OID allows bayteh traps to be sent with an IP address argument that may not be defined in the baytech MIB. A get of this OID will return 0.0.0.0.

mtrapargsString.name: mtrapargsString
mtrapargsString.description: This OID allows baytech traps to be sent with an octet string argument that may not be defined in the baytech MIB. A get of this OID will return a NULL string.

mtrapargsGauge.name: mtrapargsGauge
mtrapargsGauge.description: This OID allows baytech traps to be sent with a Gauge argument that may not be defined in the baytech MIB. A get of this OID will return 0.

mtrapargsTimeTicks.name: mtrapargsTimeTicks
mtrapargsTimeTicks.description: This OID allows baytech traps to be sent with a TimeTicks argument that may not be defined in the baytech MIB. A get of this OID will return 0.

sBTAModuleIndex.name: sBTAModuleIndex
sBTAModuleIndex.description: This OID allows baytech traps to be sent with an integer argument that may not be defined in the baytech MIB. This is an index to a specific DS module. Value will equal the slot of the module. A get of this OID will return 0.

sBTAOutletIndex.name: sBTAOutletIndex
sBTAOutletIndex.description: This OID allows baytech traps to be sent with an integer argument that may not be defined in the baytech MIB. This is an index to a specific outlet in a DS module. Value is 1 to number of outlets controlled by the ds module. 0 represents all outlets. A get of this OID will return 0.

sBTAPortIndex.name: sBTAPortIndex
sBTAPortIndex.description: This OID allows baytech traps to be sent with an integer argument that may not be defined in the baytech MIB. This is an index to a specific outlet in a DS module. Value is 1 to number of outlets controlled by the ds module. 0 represents all outlets. A get of this OID will return 0.

sBTAVoltageSource.name: sBTAVoltageSource
sBTAVoltageSource.description: This OID allows baytech traps to be sent with an integer argument that may not be defined in the baytech MIB. This is the number associated with the voltage source in an RPC. Value is 1 or 2, depending on which voltage source is powering the RPC. A get of this OID will return 0.

sBTASourceSwitchCount.name: sBTASourceSwitchCount
sBTASourceSwitchCount.description: This OID allows baytech traps to be sent with an integer argument that may not be defined in the baytech MIB. This is the number associated with the number of voltage source transitions in an RPC. Value is 0 to 255, an 8-bit w/rollover count of number of times voltage source has been switched from one source to another. A get of this OID will return 0.

sBTASensorIndex.name: sBTASensorIndex
sBTASensorIndex.description: This OID allows baytech traps to be sent with an integer argument that may not be defined in the baytech MIB. This is an index to a specific sensor in a DS module. Value is 1 to number of sensors controlled by the ds module. A get of this OID will return 0.

sBTABreakerIndex.name: sBTABreakerIndex
sBTABreakerIndex.description: This is an object which is sent along with a trap to designate a breaker number pertinent to a particular trap. This value will range from 1 to the total number of breakers inside the particular RPC. A get of this OID will return 0.

sBTAModulesRPCModPortTable.name: sBTAModulesRPCModPortTable
sBTAModulesRPCModPortTable.description: Allows for control of individual outlets and individual RPC modules. The number of entries is contained in the sBTAModulesNumberOfRPCModules OID.

sBTAModulesRPCModPortEntry.name: sBTAModulesRPCModPortEntry
sBTAModulesRPCModPortEntry.description: The RPCs to control and get status on.

sRPCModuleIndex.name: sRPCModuleIndex
sRPCModuleIndex.description: The module number index into the RPC table.

sRPCPortIndex.name: sRPCPortIndex
sRPCPortIndex.description: The port number index into the RPC table. In the case of ds30 modules this number is always 1.

sRPCType.name: sRPCType
sRPCType.description: Type of RPC at the module, port index.

sRPCName.name: sRPCName
sRPCName.description: The name (unit id) of the rpc module.

sRPCFirmwareVersion.name: sRPCFirmwareVersion
sRPCFirmwareVersion.description: The firware version of the rpc module.

sRPCCurrent.name: sRPCCurrent
sRPCCurrent.description: The current reading for the power strip. If current measurement is not installed this value will always read 0.

sRPCMaxCurrent.name: sRPCMaxCurrent
sRPCMaxCurrent.description: The maximum detected current reading for the power strip. If current measurement is not installed this value will always read 0. Setting this value to 0 will clear the maximum current detected.

sRPCVoltage.name: sRPCVoltage
sRPCVoltage.description: The voltage reading for the power strip. If voltage measurement is not installed this value will always read 0.

sRPCPower.name: sRPCPower
sRPCPower.description: The power reading for the power strip. If power measurement is not installed this value will always read 0.

sRPCTemperature.name: sRPCTemperature
sRPCTemperature.description: The temperature reading for the power strip. Readings are in degrees C. If temperature measurement is not installed this value will always read 0.

sRPCRebootTimeout.name: sRPCRebootTimeout
sRPCRebootTimeout.description: The length of off time for automatic reboot sequences. Currently a read-only value set to the fixed reboot timeout.

sRPCAllOutletsCmd.name: sRPCAllOutletsCmd
sRPCAllOutletsCmd.description: Turns all outlets on, off or reboot. 0 = off 1 = on 2 = reboot 3 = lockon (will lock outlets to on state) 4 = lockoff (will lock outlets to off state) 5 = unlock (will unlock all outlets) A get will return unknown (6).

sRPCAllOutletsStatus.name: sRPCAllOutletsStatus
sRPCAllOutletsStatus.description: Reports status of outlets in a comma deliminated string. 0 = off 1 = on 2 = reboot 3 = locked on 4 = locked off

sRPCCurrentAlarmThreshold.name: sRPCCurrentAlarmThreshold
sRPCCurrentAlarmThreshold.description: The current alarm threshold level *10. A value of 105 will set the level to 10.5.

sRPCOverVoltageThreshold.name: sRPCOverVoltageThreshold
sRPCOverVoltageThreshold.description: The over voltage alarm threshold level *10. A value of 105 will set the level to 10.5.

sRPCUnderVoltageThreshold.name: sRPCUnderVoltageThreshold
sRPCUnderVoltageThreshold.description: The under voltage alarm threshold level *10. A value of 105 will set the level to 10.5.

sRPCNumberOfOutlets.name: sRPCNumberOfOutlets
sRPCNumberOfOutlets.description: Number of outlets for this RPC. This will be the size of outlet table for this RPC index.

sRPCCircuitBreaker.name: sRPCCircuitBreaker
sRPCCircuitBreaker.description: Status of circuit breaker in power strip. 0=off 1=on.

sRPCOverTempThreshold.name: sRPCOverTempThreshold
sRPCOverTempThreshold.description: The over temperature alarm threshold level *10. A value of 505 will set the level to 50.5.

sRPCUnitVA.name: sRPCUnitVA
sRPCUnitVA.description: Number of outlets for this RPC. This will be the size of outlet table for this RPC index.

sRPCNumberOfBreakers.name: sRPCNumberOfBreakers
sRPCNumberOfBreakers.description: Number of breakers for this RPC.

sRPCLowCurrentThreshold.name: sRPCLowCurrentThreshold
sRPCLowCurrentThreshold.description: Low current threshold for this RPC.

sRPCSourceSwitchCount.name: sRPCSourceSwitchCount
sRPCSourceSwitchCount.description: Voltage source switch count for this RPC.

sRPCNumberOfSensors.name: sRPCNumberOfSensors
sRPCNumberOfSensors.description: Number of sensors for this RPC.

sBTAModulesRPCModPortOutletTable.name: sBTAModulesRPCModPortOutletTable
sBTAModulesRPCModPortOutletTable.description: Allows for control of individual outlets. The number of entries is contained in the sBTAModulesRPCOutletTableSize OID.

sBTAModulesRPCModPortOutletEntry.name: sBTAModulesRPCModPortOutletEntry
sBTAModulesRPCModPortOutletEntry.description: The outlets to control and get status on.

sRPCOutletModuleIndex.name: sRPCOutletModuleIndex
sRPCOutletModuleIndex.description: The module index to the outlet entry.

sRPCOutletPortIndex.name: sRPCOutletPortIndex
sRPCOutletPortIndex.description: The port index to the outlet entry. In the case of ds30s this number is always 1.

sRPCOutletIndex.name: sRPCOutletIndex
sRPCOutletIndex.description: The outlet index to the outlet entry.

sRPCOutletState.name: sRPCOutletState
sRPCOutletState.description: Getting this variable will return the state of the outlet. Valid return states are unknown, on, off, lockon, lockoff. 0 = off 1 = on 2 = reboot 3 = lockon (outlet is on and no changes are allowed) 4 = lockoff (outlet is off and no changes are allowed) 5 = unlock.

sRPCOutletName.name: sRPCOutletName
sRPCOutletName.description: The name of the outlet. Maximum size is 16 characters.

sBTAModulesRPCModPortGroupCmd.name: sBTAModulesRPCModPortGroupCmd
sBTAModulesRPCModPortGroupCmd.description: A character string listing the outlets that need to be rebooted, turned off, or turn on as a group. Command is the first character followed by a space. Valid commads are 0=off,1=on, or 2=reboot. A list follows the command in the format module.port.outlet. For example 2 2.1.1,2.1.12,3.4.1 will reboot module 2 port 1 outlet 2&12 module 3 port 4 outlet 1.

sRPCModPortBreakersTable.name: sRPCModPortBreakersTable
sRPCModPortBreakersTable.description: Allows monitoring of individual outlet strips on RPCs.

sRPCBreakersModIndex.name: sRPCBreakersModIndex
sRPCBreakersModIndex.description: The module index into the RPC breaker table.

sRPCBreakersPortIndex.name: sRPCBreakersPortIndex
sRPCBreakersPortIndex.description: The port index into the RPC breaker table.

sRPCBreakersBreakersIndex.name: sRPCBreakersBreakersIndex
sRPCBreakersBreakersIndex.description: The breaker index into the RPC breaker table.

sRPCBreakersCircuitBreaker.name: sRPCBreakersCircuitBreaker
sRPCBreakersCircuitBreaker.description: Status of circuit breaker in power strip. 0=off 1=on.

sRPCBreakersCurrent.name: sRPCBreakersCurrent
sRPCBreakersCurrent.description: The detected current reading for the power strip. If current measurement is not installed this value will always read 0.

sRPCBreakersMaxCurrent.name: sRPCBreakersMaxCurrent
sRPCBreakersMaxCurrent.description: The maximum detected current reading for the power strip. If current measurement is not installed this value will always read 0.

sRPCBreakersVoltage.name: sRPCBreakersVoltage
sRPCBreakersVoltage.description: The voltage reading for the power strip. If voltage measurement is not installed this value will always read 0.

sRPCBreakersPower.name: sRPCBreakersPower
sRPCBreakersPower.description: The power reading for the power strip. If voltage measurement is not installed this value will always read 0.

sRPCBreakersVA.name: sRPCBreakersVA
sRPCBreakersVA.description: The volt-amps reading for the power strip. If voltage measurement is not installed this value will always read 0.
